# Platform Status = FROZEN

The platform is mature enough to be a **support layer**, not the center of every sprint.

**95% time → Business modules. 5% time → Critical bugs.**

## DO NOT (Locked)

- Improve Platform core
- Improve ADT / generators
- Improve SDK (Plugin, Theme, AI)
- Improve Quality Gates / test framework infrastructure
- Improve Architecture / write new architecture reports
- Improve Documentation sprints
- Improve Release Reports / governance documents
- Improve Build System / CI scaffolding
- Create new Blade-first ERP screens
- Treat scaffold CRUD as "module complete"

## ONLY FIX (Platform exceptions)

- Fatal errors / crashes
- Undefined variables / type errors blocking runtime
- SQL / migration errors
- Broken routes / 404 on required APIs
- Security-critical bugs (auth bypass, injection, data leak)

Everything else on the platform is **LOCKED**.

## Product Vision (North Star)

Build an Odoo competitor, not a framework demo:

- Better UX than Odoo
- Better architecture than ERPNext
- SAP-grade Accounting (PostingEngine lock)
- Oracle-grade Security (existing RBAC/MFA)
- Dynamics-grade Integrations (after core ERP)
- React + PWA + Electron + Cloud + Marketplace + AI (phased)

## Primary ERP UI

```
REST API (Laravel)  +  React SPA (axiomos-web)
```

Blade = legacy / admin debug only. **Never** ship new product features in Blade.

## React Architecture (Required)

Every new module must use:

- Feature modules (plugin contract)
- Lazy loading / code splitting
- Plugin loader + dynamic menus
- Theme engine (dark/light)
- Permission-based routing
- Real-time notifications (when API exists)
- PWA / offline-ready shell
- Electron desktop (Phase 8 — after web ERP stable)
